WEBVTT

00:01.130 --> 00:02.688
PREVIOUSLY
ON "VERONICA MARS"...

00:02.700 --> 00:04.429
I HAVE INFORMATION ABOUT THAT
MEXICAN KID WHO GOT KILLED.

00:04.430 --> 00:06.534
I'M THE ONE WHO MADE THE
ANONYMOUS CALL FROM THE BRIDGE.

00:06.540 --> 00:08.132
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST FOR
THE MURDER OF FELIX TOOMBS.

00:08.140 --> 00:10.358
OOH, I AM HAVING
THE WEIRDEST DJ VU.

00:10.370 --> 00:12.270
LOGAN MADE BAIL IN, LIKE,
TWO MINUTES.

00:12.280 --> 00:14.532
MAYBE IT IS TIME WE DID
SOMETHING ABOUT LOGAN ECHOLLS.

00:14.540 --> 00:16.303
THE FITZPATRICKS
ARE METH-HEAD LUNATICS,

00:16.310 --> 00:18.972
BUT THEY'RE NOT GONNA KILL
A BUS FULL OF KIDS OVER 3 GRAND.

00:18.980 --> 00:20.516
THEIR PROBLEM
WITH CERVANDO

00:20.520 --> 00:22.886
WOULD HAVE BEEN SOLVED IN
AN ALLEY WITH A BASEBALL BAT.

00:22.890 --> 00:24.084
VERONICA?

00:24.090 --> 00:26.718
DUNCAN?
HOW'S MEG?

00:26.720 --> 00:30.520
IF YOU CARED ABOUT MEG, SHE
WOULDN'T HAVE BEEN ON THAT BUS.

00:33.730 --> 00:35.652
DO YOU LOVE ME?

00:37.170 --> 00:39.661
DID YOU EVER LOVE ME?

00:41.470 --> 00:47.431
ON THE BUS, MY LIFE
DIDN'T FLASH BEFORE ME.

00:47.440 --> 00:48.668
YOU DID.

00:48.680 --> 00:50.341
OUR FIRST KISS.

00:50.350 --> 00:54.775
THE LAST PERFECT MOMENT
WE HAD TOGETHER.

00:54.780 --> 00:56.589
REMEMBER?

00:56.590 --> 00:58.649
ON THE BEACH.

00:58.650 --> 01:00.857
PLEASE.

01:00.860 --> 01:03.624
YOU PROMISED ME.

01:03.630 --> 01:06.519
YOU MADE PROMISES.

01:06.530 --> 01:08.020
YOU CAN SAVE ME.

01:08.030 --> 01:10.794
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO IS WANT TO.

01:10.800 --> 01:14.861
I'VE HEARD ENOUGH.
HAVE YOU HEARD ENOUGH?

01:14.870 --> 01:16.406
WHAT DOES SHE HAVE?

01:16.410 --> 01:20.107
WHAT DOES SHE HAVE
THAT I HAVEN'T GOT?

01:20.110 --> 01:24.046
WELL, I'M CONSCIOUS,

01:24.050 --> 01:26.473
AND THAT'S
JUST FOR STARTERS.

01:26.480 --> 01:29.313
IS THAT REALLY
WHAT YOU WANT?

01:29.320 --> 01:31.982
TEDDY BEARS
AND MASH NOTES?

01:31.990 --> 01:33.685
GROW UP.

01:33.690 --> 01:35.419
GROW UP AND GET OVER IT.

01:35.420 --> 01:39.322
Veronica:
ALL I'M SAYING IS, I FOLLOWED
HIM INTO THE CIGAR SHOP,

01:39.330 --> 01:41.491
HE BOUGHT SOME CIGARS,
AND HE LEFI'.

01:41.500 --> 01:43.263
Logan:
DIDN'T YOUR DAD SAY

01:43.270 --> 01:44.897
THAT THE CIGAR STORE'S
A FRONT FOR DRUG DEALERS?

01:44.900 --> 01:47.334
THAT'S GOT
TO BE SOMETHING.
OR NOT.

01:47.340 --> 01:50.468
SOMETIMES A CIGAR STORE
IS JUST A CIGAR STORE.

01:50.470 --> 01:52.199
WELL, I'LL REMEMBER
TO BE QUIPPY

01:52.210 --> 01:53.677
WHEN YOU'RE LOOKING
AT 20 TO LIFE.

01:53.680 --> 01:56.171
OH, YOU'RE BEING
A JACKASS.

01:56.180 --> 01:57.738
IT MUST BE
AN EVEN-NUMBERED DAY.

01:57.750 --> 01:59.741
I DO SO PREFER
THE ODD-NUMBERED DAYS

01:59.750 --> 02:02.184
WHEN YOU'RE KISSING MY ASS
FOR A FAVOR.

02:02.190 --> 02:03.748
YOU FIND OUT
WHY THIS PLASTIC SURGEON

02:03.750 --> 02:06.355
IS TRYING TO GET ME SENT AWAY
FOR KILLING FELIX,

02:06.360 --> 02:08.578
AND I WILL MAKE SURE
THAT ALL EVEN-NUMBERED DAYS

02:08.590 --> 02:11.127
ARE REMOVED
FROM THE CALENDAR.

02:11.130 --> 02:12.620
DID DUNCAN GO TO BED?
YES.

02:12.630 --> 02:14.427
AND HE WANTED ME
TO TELL YOU

02:14.430 --> 02:16.466
TO GIVE ME
YOUR UNDIVIDED ATTENTION.

02:16.470 --> 02:19.689
PRETEND FOR A MOMENT THAT
YOUR DOG'S LIFE IS AT STAKE.

02:19.700 --> 02:21.292
HEY.

02:21.300 --> 02:23.609
HEY, MAYBE
THIS SO-CALLED DOCTOR

02:23.610 --> 02:26.477
IS A PIPELINE
TO PRESCRIPTION DRUGS.

02:26.480 --> 02:28.471
THAT'S HOW MY PEDIATRICIAN
LOST HIS LICENSE.

02:28.480 --> 02:32.769
WELL, IT'S PRETTY EASY
TO CHECK ON SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

02:34.480 --> 02:37.244
Meg: YOU CAN SAVE ME.

02:37.250 --> 02:39.252
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO IS WANT TO.

02:39.260 --> 02:41.649
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION
IN DISTANCE ]

02:55.600 --> 02:58.239
Veronica:
I FOUND SOMETHING.
Logan:
WHAT IS IT?

02:58.240 --> 02:59.776
WELL,
THE A.M.A. WEBSITE

02:59.780 --> 03:02.374
LISTS ANY DISCIPLINARY ACTIONS
TAKEN AGAINST ITS MEMBERS.

03:02.380 --> 03:05.599
APPARENTLY DR. GRIFFITH
WAS REPRIMANDED --

03:05.610 --> 03:09.649
SOMETHING ABOUT AN INAPPROPRIATE
OFF-SITE PRACTICE.

03:09.650 --> 03:12.414
THE PATIENT'S NAME
IS DANNY BOYD.

03:12.420 --> 03:14.615
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
I DON'T KNOW.

03:14.620 --> 03:17.327
BUT I'LL CHECK IT OUT
TOMORROW.

03:18.590 --> 03:23.027
HEY, MAN, YOU GOT
THE STUFF IN YET?

03:23.030 --> 03:24.361
I'M, LIKE, WONDERING

03:24.370 --> 03:27.089
IF I NEED TO TAKE MY BUSINESS
ELSEWHERE.

03:27.100 --> 03:28.397
WHAT STUFF?

03:28.400 --> 03:30.561
I, UH, ORDERED
AN EIGHT BALL.

03:30.570 --> 03:31.502
COKE?

03:31.510 --> 03:34.638
WHO AM I,
JOHN DeLOREAN?

03:34.640 --> 03:36.972
I NEVER SOLD COKE
TO YOU, MAN.

03:39.680 --> 03:41.671
HEY, THIS IS
A $200 SHIRT, MAN!

03:41.680 --> 03:44.285
REALLY?
IT'S MISSING SOME BUTTONS.

03:44.290 --> 03:46.508
HEY, COME ON.
DON'T JERK ME AROUND.

03:46.520 --> 03:48.852
I PAID ONE
OF YOU BIKER GUYS.
OH, YEAH?

03:48.860 --> 03:51.556
DESCRIBE THIS BIKER GUY
YOU PAID.

03:51.560 --> 03:55.792
I DON'T KNOW.
HE WAS, YOU KNOW, BROWN.

03:57.670 --> 03:59.661
HEY, THOSE
ARE NICE RIMS.

03:59.670 --> 04:03.766
YOU KNOW, I WAS THINKING ABOUT
GETTING ME SOME JUST LIKE THOSE.

04:06.310 --> 04:07.902
[ CAR ALARM ACT IVATES ]

04:12.050 --> 04:13.449
Carlos: OUR SON MARCOS

04:13.450 --> 04:15.338
WAS ONE OF THE STUDENTS
KILLED IN THE BUS CRASH.

04:15.350 --> 04:17.682
I AM TRULY SORRY.

04:18.720 --> 04:21.587
FOR THE PAST THREE MONTHS,
WE'VE BEEN GRIEVING,

04:21.590 --> 04:23.922
TRYING TO PUT OUR LIVES
BACK TOGETHER AGAIN.

04:23.930 --> 04:26.751
HE -- HE WAS OUR ONLY CHILD,
OUR PRIDE AND JOY.

04:26.760 --> 04:30.093
I CAN ONLY IMAGINE
HOW DIFFICULT THAT MUST BE.

04:30.100 --> 04:31.795
THEN TRY TO IMAGINE

04:31.800 --> 04:33.631
IF SOMEONE WAS DOING THEIR BEST
NOT TO LET YOU FORGET.

04:33.640 --> 04:35.835
I'M NOT SURE
I UNDERSTAND.

04:35.840 --> 04:38.001
WE'RE BEING HARASSED,
MR. MARS.

04:38.010 --> 04:43.300
SOMEONE IS BREAKING INTO
OUR HOUSE AND LEAVING THESE.

04:44.910 --> 04:46.411
WELL, THAT'S HORRIBLE.

04:46.420 --> 04:47.910
WE'LL COME HOME,
AND THE HOUSE

04:47.920 --> 04:50.684
WILL SMELL LIKE THE COLOGNE
THAT MARCOS USED TO WEAR.

04:50.690 --> 04:53.750
MARCOS' PICTURES WILL BE
TURNED AROUND IN THEIR FRAMES.

04:53.760 --> 04:55.887
AND THAT'S NOT
THE WORST PART.

04:55.890 --> 04:59.758
WE'VE BEEN GETTING MESSAGES
ON OUR VOICE MAIL FROM OUR SON.

04:59.760 --> 05:02.558
WE DON'T BELIEVE IN GHOSTS,
MR. MARS.

05:02.570 --> 05:04.197
OUR SON IS DEAD.

05:04.200 --> 05:05.724
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

05:05.730 --> 05:10.633
MESSAGES ARE JUST NONSENSE --
OLD RECORDINGS OF MARCOS.

05:10.640 --> 05:13.529
WE SHOULD JUST
TAKE NED'S OFFER, CARLOS,

05:13.540 --> 05:14.802
AND SELL THE HOUSE.

05:14.810 --> 05:17.370
WE HAVE NOTHING
KEEPING US HERE.

05:17.380 --> 05:20.042
WE DON'T RUN, MARIA.

05:20.050 --> 05:22.018
THAT'S NOT US.

05:24.420 --> 05:25.717
SO, I'M ASSUMING
YOU WANT ME

05:25.720 --> 05:27.608
TO FIND OUT
WHO'S BEEN HARASSING YOU.

05:27.620 --> 05:29.827
OH, I KNOW
WHO'S HARASSING US.

05:29.830 --> 05:32.754
I WANT YOU
TO FIND THE PROOF.

05:35.860 --> 05:37.589
Veronica:
THIS IS IT.

05:37.600 --> 05:40.592
THE OWNER OF THIS DUMP'S
A FRONT FOR PLASTIC SURGERY?

05:40.600 --> 05:42.568
UNH-UNH.
YOU'RE STAYING HERE.

05:42.570 --> 05:44.663
THIS TAKES
A CERTAIN SUBTLETY.

05:44.670 --> 05:48.128
BUT IF I NEED ANYONE
PUNCHED IN THE FACE,

05:48.140 --> 05:49.949
I'LL WHISTLE FOR YOU.

05:58.220 --> 05:59.482
DAN NY BOYD?
YEAH.

05:59.490 --> 06:00.912
MY NAME
IS LAURIE ZACHS.

06:00.920 --> 06:02.729
I DON'T NEED
TO KNOW YOUR NAME, HONEY.

06:02.730 --> 06:04.379
JUST TELL ME YOU'RE 18.

06:04.390 --> 06:05.550
ACTUALLY --

06:05.560 --> 06:08.290
OH, WHO'S KIDDING WHO?
LIKE I CARE.

06:08.300 --> 06:10.689
OKAY, UH,
THE REASON I'M HERE --

06:10.700 --> 06:13.635
I WAS CONSIDERING
HAVING DR. TOM GRIFFITH

06:13.640 --> 06:15.961
PERFORM A SURGICAL PROCEDURE
ON ME,

06:15.970 --> 06:17.665
AND I'M
ONE OF THOSE PEOPLE

06:17.670 --> 06:19.934
WHO REALLY LIKES
TO CHECK A DOCTOR OUT.

06:19.940 --> 06:21.202
DR. GRIFFITH, HUH?

06:21.210 --> 06:22.871
HE'S A GOOD MAN, BUT I WOULDN'T
GO GETTING TOO CRAZY

06:22.880 --> 06:24.973
'CAUSE YOU DON'T NEED
VERY MUCH WORK DONE, YOU KNOW,

06:24.980 --> 06:26.447
BESIDES THE OBVIOUS.

06:26.450 --> 06:28.213
YEAH, THANKS.

06:28.220 --> 06:31.018
UM, I NOTICED HE WAS GIVEN
A MEDICAL REPRIMAND

06:31.020 --> 06:33.409
FOR A PROCEDURE
HE DID ON YOU,

06:33.420 --> 06:36.150
AND I JUST WANTED
TO SEE --
DID HE GET
IN TROUBLE FOR THAT?

06:36.160 --> 06:39.789
I'M GUESSING IT HAD
TO DO WITH YOUR FACE.

06:39.800 --> 06:40.994
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:41.000 --> 06:44.891
YOU THINK, HUH?
NO. COME ON. I'LL SHOW YOU.

06:53.340 --> 06:55.171
[ DOG BARKING ]

07:04.790 --> 07:07.588
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]

07:09.320 --> 07:10.856
Veronica: GREAT.

07:10.860 --> 07:13.021
I'VE WALKED RIGHT
INTO THE RIVER STYX --

07:13.030 --> 07:15.749
HOME BASE FOR
THE FIGHTING FITZPATRICKS,

07:15.760 --> 07:18.228
NEPTUNE'S FIRST FAMILY
OF CRIME.

07:18.230 --> 07:20.289
COME HERE.

07:20.300 --> 07:21.892
COME HERE.

07:21.900 --> 07:23.265
CHECK IT OUT.

07:23.270 --> 07:24.532
TAKE A LOOK.

07:24.540 --> 07:27.737
[ Chuckling ]
THAT'S MY BLOOD.

07:27.740 --> 07:30.300
CAN YOU DIG THAT?

07:30.310 --> 07:31.948
WHAT HAPPENED?

07:31.950 --> 07:33.872
IT WAS A LITTLE
BAR FIGHT.

07:33.880 --> 07:36.519
YEAH, YOU SHOULD SEE
THE OTHER GUY.

07:36.520 --> 07:38.647
I GOT 45 STITCHES.
GOOD AS NEW.

07:38.650 --> 07:40.709
A PLASTIC SURGEON
DID THAT?

07:40.720 --> 07:42.585
HE WASN'T TRYING
TO MAKE IT LOOK PRETTY,

07:42.590 --> 07:44.319
JUST TRYING
TO STOP THE BLEEDING.

07:44.330 --> 07:45.979
AND DR. GRIFFITH'S --

07:45.990 --> 07:47.753
HEY, LIAM. LIAM.

07:47.760 --> 07:49.398
WHAT DO YOU CALL
THE GOOD DOCTOR?

07:49.400 --> 07:51.391
HE'S KIND OF LIKE A "FRIEND
OF THE FAMILY" TYPE THING?

07:51.400 --> 07:54.392
MY NIECE MOLLY -- SHE SAW
THE BLOOD, SHE GOT FREAKED OUT.

07:54.400 --> 07:56.709
AND SHE CALLED AN AMBULANCE.
I GOT THREE MONTHS IN COUNTY.

07:56.710 --> 07:58.132
I GUESS THE DOCTOR GOT
IN TROUBLE, TOO, HUH?

07:58.140 --> 08:00.734
OH, WELL, ALL'S WELL
THAT ENDS WELL, RIGHT?

08:00.740 --> 08:03.868
I MEAN, IT'S A CONVERSATION
PIECE, THAT'S FOR SURE.

08:03.880 --> 08:07.646
WHO ARE YOU?
UH, LAURIE.
HER NAME'S --

08:07.650 --> 08:09.470
WHO ARE YOU?

08:09.480 --> 08:10.947
UH, I'M LAURIE.

08:10.950 --> 08:13.282
SHE'S GETTING SOME
PLASTIC SURGERY DONE BY --

08:13.290 --> 08:15.758
HER NAME'S NOT LAURIE.
IT'S VERONICA MARS.

08:15.760 --> 08:19.992
SHE GOES TO MY SCHOOL.
SHE'S KEITH MARS' DAUGHTER.

08:21.230 --> 08:23.221
GO, PIRATES.

08:23.230 --> 08:24.424
VERONICA?

08:24.430 --> 08:26.159
WELL, YOU'RE ABOUT
TO TELL ME

08:26.170 --> 08:28.832
THE REAL REASON YOU'RE
ASKING ABOUT DR. GRIFFITH.

08:28.840 --> 08:31.035
YOU LIE TO ME AGAIN,

08:31.040 --> 08:33.304
AND YOU REALLY WILL NEED
A GOOD PLASTIC SURGEON.

08:33.310 --> 08:36.609
* TONIGHT THERE'S GONNA
BE TROUBLE *

08:39.110 --> 08:43.114
* A LONG TIME AGO,
WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

08:43.120 --> 08:48.410
* BUT I HAVEN'T THOUGHT OF YOU
LATELY AT ALL *

08:49.120 --> 08:51.224
* COME ON, NOW, SUGAR *

08:51.230 --> 08:53.790
* BRING IT ON, BRING IT ON,
YEAH *

08:53.800 --> 08:57.258
* JUST REMEMBER ME WHEN *

08:57.270 --> 09:02.298
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS
A LONG TIME AGO *

09:02.300 --> 09:04.359
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

09:04.370 --> 09:07.999
-- Captions by VITAC --
www.vitac.com

09:11.810 --> 09:13.038
TELL ME WHY YOU'RE HERE,
VERONICA.

09:13.050 --> 09:14.813
WHAT, DID SOMEONE
SEND YOU?

09:14.820 --> 09:17.516
IT'S -- IT REALLY IS
PLASTIC SURGERY.

09:17.520 --> 09:21.308
I DIDN'T WANT TO USE MY NAME
BECAUSE IT WAS TOO EMBARRASSING.

09:21.320 --> 09:22.628
YOU'RE A GOOD LIAR.

09:22.630 --> 09:26.179
IT'S GONNA MAKE THINGS
SO MUCH TOUGHER.

09:40.880 --> 09:42.802
OH, ALL RIGHT, THEN.

09:42.810 --> 09:45.074
THAT WAS FUN.

09:45.080 --> 09:47.571
BUT LET'S NOT
STOP THERE.

09:47.580 --> 09:50.686
MONK, MONK,
BRING IT HERE!

09:53.360 --> 09:57.148
SO, WHAT'S IT GONNA BE,
VERONICA? HMM?

09:57.160 --> 10:00.618
PINK MOON?
YELLOW STARS?

10:00.630 --> 10:01.722
NO?

10:01.730 --> 10:03.561
A GREEN CLOVER OR DAISY?

10:03.570 --> 10:06.266
I'M JUST GONNA START IN
OVER HERE.

10:06.270 --> 10:11.037
AS SOON AS I HEAR SOMETHING
RESEMBLING THE TRUTH, I'LL STOP.

10:11.040 --> 10:13.031
HEY!
I'VE GOT 911 ON THE LINE.

10:13.040 --> 10:15.508
WHO CAN GIVE ME
THE ADDRESS HERE?

10:15.510 --> 10:17.444
NO ONE?!

10:17.450 --> 10:19.748
YEAH, I'VE GOT ONE
OF THOSE ANKLE MONITORS ON.

10:19.750 --> 10:20.910
DOES THAT HELP?

10:20.920 --> 10:23.411
YEAH.
THE RIVER STYX.

10:23.420 --> 10:25.786
THERE'S BLOOD EVERYWHERE.

10:25.790 --> 10:27.280
VERONICA, LET'S GO.

10:27.290 --> 10:29.850
WELL, LADS, LET SEE
HOW MUCH DAMAGE WE CAN DO

10:29.860 --> 10:31.919
IN THE NEXT TWO MINUTES.
STOP!

10:34.960 --> 10:37.565
I'VE HAD A VERY BAD YEAR.

10:37.570 --> 10:41.461
* SO TAKE A LOOK AT ME NOW *

10:41.470 --> 10:43.859
* SO TAKE A LOOK AT ME NOW *

10:43.870 --> 10:47.203
* SO TAKE A LOOK AT ME NOW *

10:47.210 --> 10:50.247
* SO TAKE A LOOK AT ME NOW *

10:50.250 --> 10:53.344
* SO TAKE A LOOK AT ME NOW *

10:53.350 --> 10:54.908
* NOW, NOW *

11:07.700 --> 11:09.827
[ CRYING ]

11:11.400 --> 11:14.790
HEY, IT'S OKAY.

11:14.800 --> 11:16.961
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

11:16.970 --> 11:18.528
A GUN, LOGAN?!
A GUN?!

11:18.540 --> 11:20.531
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
WITH A GUN?!

11:20.540 --> 11:22.599
YOU'RE GONNA
GET YOURSELF KILLED!

11:22.610 --> 11:24.441
DON'T YOU
UNDERSTAND THAT?!

11:24.450 --> 11:26.145
LOOK, IT'S NOT
EVEN LOADED.

11:26.150 --> 11:28.015
OH, I FEEL
SO MUCH BETTER.

11:28.020 --> 11:30.648
DICK'S DAD GAVE IT TO ME.
HE SAID GIVEN MY SITUATION --

11:30.650 --> 11:35.314
GIVEN YOUR SITUATION, YOU
SHOULD JUST MOVE OUT OF NEPTUNE.

11:35.320 --> 11:39.029
YEAH, WELL, NO CAN DO.

11:52.310 --> 11:55.131
Keith: HONEY?

11:55.140 --> 11:57.677
DID YOU KNOW
MARCOS OLIVERAS?

11:57.680 --> 12:00.148
UM, SHOULD I?

12:00.150 --> 12:03.085
YEAH.
HE WAS ON THE BUS.

12:03.850 --> 12:05.147
HEY, ARE YOU OKAY?

12:05.150 --> 12:08.358
TOUGH DAY.
BUT, YEAH, I'M FINE.

12:08.360 --> 12:12.023
UM, WHAT ABOUT
MARCOS OLIVERAS?

12:12.030 --> 12:13.622
HIS PARENTS
WERE JUST IN,

12:13.630 --> 12:16.155
AND THEY'RE SUING THE
SCHOOL DISTRICT FOR NEGLIGENCE

12:16.160 --> 12:17.696
OVER THEIR SON'S DEATH.

12:17.700 --> 12:20.430
AND SINCE THEY'VE FILED
THE SUIT, THEY'VE BEEN HARASSED.

12:20.440 --> 12:22.032
HARASSED?

12:22.040 --> 12:23.905
TOY BUSES
LEI-T IN THEIR HOUSE,

12:23.910 --> 12:27.471
THEIR SON'S COLOGNE
LINGERING IN THE AIR,

12:27.480 --> 12:30.369
PHONE MESSAGES FROM THEIR
DEAD SON ON THE MACHINE.

12:30.380 --> 12:32.644
SO, WHAT, THE SCHOOL DISTRICT
ADMINISTRATION

12:32.650 --> 12:35.448
IS HARASSING THEM TO GET THEM
TO DROP THEIR SUIT?

12:35.450 --> 12:37.338
I'M SURE THOSE
SCHOOL ADMINISTRATORS

12:37.350 --> 12:39.318
ARE A SINISTER
AND VENAL BUNCH, HONEY,

12:39.320 --> 12:41.811
BUT IN MY EXPERIENCE,
MOST CRIME IS PERSONAL --

12:41.820 --> 12:45.381
NOT THESE
WEIRD CONSPIRACIES.

12:45.390 --> 12:46.584
WELL, IN MY EXPERIENCE,

12:46.590 --> 12:49.525
THAT IS EXACTLY WHAT THEY
WANT YOU TO THINK.

12:49.530 --> 12:51.259
WELL, ALL THE SAME.

12:51.270 --> 12:55.331
DO YOU MIND ASKING AROUND
ABOUT THE KID?

12:55.340 --> 12:57.331
MARCOS OLIVERAS?

12:57.340 --> 12:58.329
NO ONE?

12:58.340 --> 13:00.433
NO ONE
CAN TELL ME ANYTHING?

13:00.440 --> 13:01.873
HE WAS IN THIS CLASS.

13:01.880 --> 13:04.849
IT'S FOR AN ARTICLE
FOR THE NAVIGATOR.

13:04.850 --> 13:07.842
Boy: HERE'S THE TRUTH
ABOUT MARCOS.

13:07.850 --> 13:09.408
HE NEVER SAID ANYTHING
TO ANYONE.

13:09.420 --> 13:11.479
HE JUST KIND OF GOOFED OFF
WITH THE EQUIPMENT

13:11.490 --> 13:12.684
AND KEPT TO HIMSELF.

13:12.690 --> 13:15.818
NO ONE REALLY KNEW HIM.

13:18.560 --> 13:23.065
"MARCOS OLIVERAS --
NOT PICTURED."

13:24.430 --> 13:28.537
WHAT WOULD IT BE LIKE
TO BE SIMPLY...

13:28.540 --> 13:30.132
FORGOTTEN?

13:30.140 --> 13:31.664
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

13:31.670 --> 13:33.171
PLEASE BE WALLACE AGAIN

13:33.180 --> 13:34.829
AND PLEASE BE MORE

13:34.840 --> 13:37.775
THAN THE BRUSH-OFFY "I JUST
NEED SOME TIME TO THINK"

13:37.780 --> 13:39.873
HE FINALLY SENT ME YESTERDAY.

13:39.880 --> 13:41.814
NO SUCH LUCK.

13:41.820 --> 13:44.709
"I HEARD YOU'RE DOING AN
ARTICLE ABOUT MARCOS.

13:44.720 --> 13:47.655
"I FIGURED YOU PROBABLY
DIDN'T GET MUCH INFORMATION,

13:47.660 --> 13:49.184
"SO I WANTED TO SEND A NOTE

13:49.190 --> 13:50.987
"SO AT LEAST YOU HAD ONE THING
TO QUOTE.

13:50.990 --> 13:52.685
"MARCOS WAS GREAT.
"KINDA SHY,

13:52.690 --> 13:55.352
"BUT REALLY INTERESTING
ONCE YOU GOT TO KNOW HIM.

13:55.360 --> 13:58.727
"SORRY NOT TO SIGN THIS, BUT
I'VE GOT A JEALOUS BOYFRIEND

13:58.730 --> 14:00.368
WHO KNEW I LIKED HIM, SO..."

14:00.370 --> 14:01.598
Keith: WHAT?

14:01.600 --> 14:03.431
THIS IS THE THIRD TIME
I CALLED THIS WEEK.

14:03.440 --> 14:06.932
I SENT THE DAMN THING BACK
TO YOU GUYS TWO WEEKS AGO!

14:08.840 --> 14:11.206
LOOK, I TOLD THE FIRST PERSON
MY NAME.

14:11.210 --> 14:12.472
DON'T YOU TALK
TO EACH OTHER?

14:12.480 --> 14:14.141
YOU'VE GOT
THE SERIAL NUMBER.

14:14.150 --> 14:15.913
YOU'VE GOT EVERYTHING
ON THOSE DAMN DATA BANKS!

14:15.920 --> 14:18.980
IT'S ON THE COMPUTER SCREEN
RIGHT IN FRONT OF YOUR FACE!

14:18.990 --> 14:21.185
IT SAYS WHAT?!

14:22.660 --> 14:25.527
OH, SORRY.
MY FAULT. BYE.

14:25.530 --> 14:27.794
WHY MUST YOU MAKE
THE TECH-SUPPORT PEOPLE CRY?

14:27.800 --> 14:29.199
MM.

14:29.200 --> 14:31.725
I FOUND THIS MP3 PLAYER
UNDER MRS. OLIVERAS' CAR

14:31.730 --> 14:35.131
PLAYING A LOOP OF HER
SON'S VOICE OVER HER CAR RADIO.

14:35.140 --> 14:37.438
THAT'S CREEPY...

14:37.440 --> 14:39.704
AND BIZARRE.

14:39.710 --> 14:41.871
AND IT GETS BIZARRER.

14:42.640 --> 14:45.768
THIS WAS PAID FOR BY
THE NEPTUNE SCHOOL DISTRICT.

14:45.780 --> 14:48.874
YOU MIND HAVING A CHAT
WITH THE MAN TOMORROW?

14:48.880 --> 14:52.509
AND I'LL VISIT
TECH SUPPORT, TOO.

14:56.220 --> 14:58.586
IT'S JUST WE'RE DOING AN ARTICLE
FOR THE NAVIGATOR

14:58.590 --> 15:00.592
ON THE PARENTS' REACTION
TO THE BUS CRASH.

15:00.600 --> 15:02.420
LOOK, I'M JUST
A VICE-PRINCIPAL.

15:02.430 --> 15:03.988
ANYTHING I SAY
ON THE SUBJECT

15:04.000 --> 15:06.264
HAS TO BE CLEARED
BY THE PRINCIPAL, SO --

15:06.270 --> 15:07.692
SO YOU'RE JUST
A POWERLESS FACT OTUM,

15:07.700 --> 15:10.168
AND I SHOULD TALK
TO PRINCIPAL MOOREHEAD?

15:10.170 --> 15:12.058
YES.

15:12.070 --> 15:14.470
EXACTLY.

15:14.480 --> 15:17.278
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

15:17.280 --> 15:18.747
IT'S A HORRIBLE TRAGEDY.

15:18.750 --> 15:21.913
I SYMPATHIZE WITH
THESE FAMILIES, I REALLY DO.

15:21.920 --> 15:26.414
WE MADE SETTLEMENT OFFERS, BUT
THE OLIVERASES INSIST ON SUING.

15:26.420 --> 15:28.559
NOW, IF THEY WIN
THEIR SUIT

15:28.560 --> 15:31.381
AND THE SUM THAT
THEY'RE ASKING FOR,

15:31.390 --> 15:35.929
WE'RE TALKING NO BAND,
NO ART CLASSES, FEWER STAFF.

15:35.930 --> 15:39.263
SO, YES, WE TAKE THIS
VERY SERIOUSLY.

15:39.270 --> 15:42.535
YOU ARE AWARE THAT AN MP3 PLAYER
REGISTERED TO THE SCHOOL

15:42.540 --> 15:45.134
WAS FOUND BROADCASTING
MARCOS OLIVERAS' VOICE

15:45.140 --> 15:46.368
IN HIS MOTHER CAR?

15:46.370 --> 15:48.008
WE WOULD KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT THAT.

15:48.010 --> 15:52.174
NOW, IF YOU HAVE FURTHER
QUESTIONS ON THE TOPIC,

15:52.180 --> 15:56.549
I'LL JUST REFER YOU
TO THE DISTRICT '5 LAWYERS.

15:56.550 --> 15:59.678
SIMON AND STERN --
THEY'RE BIG.

15:59.690 --> 16:04.184
AS I SAID, WE TAKE THIS
VERY SERIOUSLY.

16:05.060 --> 16:07.290
SO WHAT I'M TRYING
TO FIGURE OUT IS,

16:07.300 --> 16:11.396
IS THERE ANY WAY TO TELL WHERE
OR WHEN A RECORDING WAS MADE?

16:12.570 --> 16:16.131
Captain Krunk: OKAY, FOLKS,
THAT'S IT FOR ME. I'M OUT.

16:16.140 --> 16:17.368
OH, HEY, THIS GUY?

16:17.370 --> 16:19.634
YOU KNOW HIM?
IT'S CAPTAIN KRUNK.

16:19.640 --> 16:21.278
CAPTAIN KRUNK?

16:21.280 --> 16:23.441
YEAH, HE'S ONE OF THE GUYS
ON "AHOY MATEY'S."

16:23.450 --> 16:26.305
"AHOY MATEY'S" --
IT'S A PIRATE RADIO SHOW,

16:26.310 --> 16:28.312
THIS WEIRD
SORT OF CULT THING.

16:28.320 --> 16:29.912
THERE'S THESE TWO GUYS --

16:29.920 --> 16:31.911
CAPTAIN KRUNK
AND IMITATION CRAB --

16:31.920 --> 16:35.356
WHO JUST TALKED A LOT OF BIZARRE
SMACK ABOUT NEPTUNE HIGH.

16:35.360 --> 16:38.727
IF YOU KNEW ABOUT IT,
CAPTAIN KRUNK'S TOTALLY A STAR.

16:38.730 --> 16:41.551
WAIT. WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT MARCOS OLIVERAS.

16:41.560 --> 16:44.666
I CAN'T FIND A SINGLE PERSON
AT SCHOOL WHO HEARD HIM TALK,

16:44.670 --> 16:46.023
AND NOW YOU'RE TELLING ME

16:46.030 --> 16:47.895
THAT HE'S THE HOWARD STERN
OF NEPTUNE HIGH?

16:47.900 --> 16:52.109
YOU DIDN'T WANT TO GET
ON CAPTAIN KRUNK'S BAD SIDE.

16:52.110 --> 16:53.668
HE'D TEAR YOU A NEW ONE.

16:53.680 --> 16:57.104
TRYING TO TELL IT LIKE IT IS.
THE TRUTH HURTS.

16:57.110 --> 16:58.748
I'M OUT.

17:01.750 --> 17:03.479
Captain Krunk: "AHOY MATEY'S" --
540 ON YOUR A.M. DIAL.

17:03.490 --> 17:06.015
LISTEN OR WALK
MY ENORMOUS PLANK.

17:06.020 --> 17:07.578
OH, I GET IT.

17:07.590 --> 17:10.479
IT'S NOT ALL CROTCH-GRABBING,
SCATOLOGICAL MAN HUMOR.

17:10.490 --> 17:11.980
THERE'S A LITTLE SOMETHING
FOR EVERYONE.

17:11.990 --> 17:14.129
FLATULENT SOUND EFFECTS
FOR ME?

17:14.130 --> 17:16.598
AND BITTER TIRADES
FOR ME.

17:16.600 --> 17:18.625
I'LL DOWNLOAD A FEW EPISODES
FOR YOU.

17:18.630 --> 17:20.063
THEY AIR EVERY THURSDAY.

17:20.070 --> 17:21.662
WHAT'S THIS
4-WEEK GAP HERE?

17:21.670 --> 17:23.968
OH, THEY WENT ON
A LITTLE SABBATICAL.

17:23.970 --> 17:25.835
DO YOU KNOW WHY?
I SUSPECT TO TORTURE ME.

17:25.840 --> 17:28.707
THEN THEY CAME BACK, AND
CAPTAIN KRUNK WASN'T ON ANYMORE,

17:28.710 --> 17:30.849
AND IT BLEW,
SO I STOPPED LISTENING.

17:30.850 --> 17:32.374
THE SHOW'S STILL ON?

17:32.380 --> 17:34.348
A BASTARDIZED SUBPAR VERSION
OF THE SHOW IS STILL ON.

17:34.350 --> 17:36.978
ANY WAY TO FIND OUT WHERE
THEY'RE BROADCASTING FROM?

17:36.980 --> 17:38.641
YES.

17:39.450 --> 17:42.214
SORRY, I WAS SEEING HOW LONG
WE COULD HAVE A CONVERSATION

17:42.220 --> 17:44.256
WITH YOUR SIDE
ONLY BEING QUESTIONS.

17:44.260 --> 17:45.284
[ SCOFFS ]

17:45.290 --> 17:47.690
WE CAN TRACK THE SIGNAL.

17:51.300 --> 17:52.824
I'D BE INTERESTED TO KNOW

17:52.830 --> 17:57.108
IF YOU HAD THE CAPABILITIES
TO TRACK SAID SIGNAL.

17:58.840 --> 18:03.174
LOOK, I'M HAPPY TO BE THE "Q"
TO YOUR BOND, BUT CRIME PAYS.

18:03.180 --> 18:05.899
TECH NOLOGICALLY ASSISTED
MYSTERY SOLVING COSTS.

18:05.910 --> 18:08.845
IF YOU WANT TO PLAY "FIND
THE CRAPPY RADIO BROADCAST,"

18:08.850 --> 18:11.819
MAMA'S GONNA NEED A FEW THINGS
FROM RADIO SHACK.

18:14.060 --> 18:16.620
LISTEN AND LOVE,
MY FRIEND.

18:16.620 --> 18:19.350
Captain Krunk:
AND HERE IT COMES.

18:19.360 --> 18:20.554
IMITATION CRAB.

18:20.560 --> 18:22.448
Imitation Crab:
ARR!

18:22.460 --> 18:24.325
THE WINNER OF THIS WEEK'S
"COCK OF THE WALK" COUNTDOWN --

18:24.330 --> 18:25.968
DON'T LEAVE THEM HANGING,
CAPTAIN.

18:25.970 --> 18:27.528
IT'S LOGAN ECHOLLS.

18:27.540 --> 18:28.939
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

18:28.940 --> 18:30.362
THAT'S 40 WEEKS RUNNING.

18:30.370 --> 18:32.201
"ROSEMARY'S BABY:
THE TEEN YEARS."

18:32.210 --> 18:34.872
IF I WAS HIS MOTHER,
I'D KILL MYSELF, TOO.

18:34.880 --> 18:36.575
[ SPLASH ]

18:36.580 --> 18:38.673
SERIOUSLY, CAPTAIN,
YOU NAME YOUR DAUGHTER ROXIE,

18:38.680 --> 18:40.341
AND IT'S GUARANTEED
AT SOME POINT

18:40.350 --> 18:41.772
SHE'LL BE SHOWING HER CANS
FOR CASH.

18:41.780 --> 18:43.782
I'M SAVING UP
FOR THAT VERY DAY.

18:43.790 --> 18:45.678
OR GET A VARSITY JACKET AND
FOUR LITERS OF WINE COOLERS,

18:45.690 --> 18:47.453
YOU CAN SEE THEM
FOR FREE.

18:47.460 --> 18:49.519
YEAH, BECKER'S A DATE RAPIST,
BUT IN HIS DEFENSE,

18:49.520 --> 18:52.023
HE'S HIDEOUS AND STUPID,
SO MEETING GIRLS IS HARD.

18:52.030 --> 18:54.191
IT SEEMS TAYLOR READ THE FINE
PRINT IN OUR ABSTINENCE PLEDGE

18:54.200 --> 18:58.728
AND FOUND A FEW -- WHAT'S
THE WORD, LOOP SOMETHING? --

18:58.730 --> 19:00.266
OH, RIGHT -- HOLES.

19:00.270 --> 19:02.989
Veronica: CAPTAIN KRUNK BAGGED
ON EVERYONE AT SCHOOL.

19:03.000 --> 19:04.501
SO, WHAT IF SOMEONE FOUND OUT?

19:04.510 --> 19:06.432
SUDDENLY I'VE GONE
FROM TRYING TO FIND OUT

19:06.440 --> 19:08.203
IF ANYONE MIGHT HAVE IT IN
FOR MARCOS

19:08.210 --> 19:10.974
TO WONDERING IF THERE'S ANYONE
AT SCHOOL WHO DOESN'T.

19:10.980 --> 19:13.312
DUNCAN KANE, YOU CAN'T BE
THAT RICH AND THAT PLEASANT

19:13.320 --> 19:14.912
WITHOUT HARBORING
A DARK SECRET.

19:14.920 --> 19:17.013
WHAT DO YOU THINK, CRAB?
SERIAL MURDERER?

19:17.020 --> 19:18.817
PUPPY STRANGLER?

19:18.820 --> 19:20.185
GIRLFRIEND IGNORER?

19:20.190 --> 19:22.613
WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO DUNCAN?

19:24.260 --> 19:27.081
ANY NEWS
ON NICK SCHMUCK?

19:27.090 --> 19:28.523
IT'S PRETTY CLEAR,
ISN'T IT?

19:28.530 --> 19:30.725
OUR FAVORITE PLASTIC SURGEON,
FOR WHATEVER REASON,

19:30.730 --> 19:33.198
SEEMS TO OWNED
BY THE FIGHTING FITZPATRICKS.

19:33.200 --> 19:34.599
WELL, AS FAR AS I KNOW,

19:34.600 --> 19:36.739
I'VE DONE NOTHING
TO GET THEIR IRISH UP.

19:36.740 --> 19:38.799
AND I'M WORKING ON
THE CONNECTIONS, OKAY?

19:38.810 --> 19:41.608
IF YOU COULD EXONERATE ME
SOMETIME SOON, THAT'D BE GREAT.

19:44.580 --> 19:46.571
IF YOU WANT A TOP,
I'M SURE IT'S NEGOTIABLE.

19:46.580 --> 19:50.482
HELP ME, MARS-WAN KENOBI.
YOU'RE MY ONLY HOPE.

20:02.260 --> 20:04.421
BUT WHERE'S THE VILLAINOUS
HAND-WRINGING

20:04.430 --> 20:05.692
AND MANIACAL LAUGH?

20:05.700 --> 20:08.533
YOU KNOW, YOU SHOULD
BE NICER TO ME.

20:08.540 --> 20:10.906
OR YOU'LL HUFF AND PUFF
AND BURN MY HOUSE DOWN?

20:10.910 --> 20:12.707
YOU LIED TO ME.

20:12.710 --> 20:16.703
WHAT, ARE YOU WORKING
FOR THE FITZPATRICKS NOW?

20:16.710 --> 20:17.972
LIED?

20:17.980 --> 20:20.448
I'D BE DEAD BEFORE
I WORKED FOR THOSE MICKS.

20:20.450 --> 20:22.145
"METH-UPPED LUNATICS,"
I BELIEVE,

20:22.150 --> 20:23.742
IS WHAT YOU CALLED THEM
BEFORE,

20:23.750 --> 20:26.139
GIVING ME THE IMPRESSION THAT
YOU DIDN'T GET ALONG SO NICE.

20:26.150 --> 20:27.754
SO IMAGINE MY SURPRISE

20:27.760 --> 20:30.627
WHEN THE NEW STAR WITNESS
IN FELIX'S MURDER CASE

20:30.630 --> 20:33.155
TURNS OUT TO BE
A FITZPATRICK PUPPET.

20:33.160 --> 20:35.856
THEY'RE SCRATCHING
YOUR BACK.

20:35.860 --> 20:40.229
MY QUESTION IS, HOW ARE YOU
SCRATCHING TH EIRS?

20:44.170 --> 20:46.559
OKAY. I'M HERE.
WHAT DO WE DO?

20:46.570 --> 20:48.731
YOU GOT YOUR SIGNAL
DIALED IN, RIGHT?

20:48.740 --> 20:50.105
YEP.

20:50.110 --> 20:52.374
OKAY, THE STATION ONLY HAS,
LIKE, A 2-MILE RADIUS,

20:52.380 --> 20:54.075
SO JUST KEEP WALKING

20:54.080 --> 20:56.275
IN THE DIRECTION THAT GIVES YOU
THE STRONGEST SIGNAL.

20:56.280 --> 20:58.589
WAIT.

20:58.590 --> 21:02.219
WAIT IF NERD HUNTERS DRIVE BY
AND TRANQ AND TAG ME?

21:02.220 --> 21:04.450
THAT'S A RISK
I'M WILLING TO TAKE.

21:05.490 --> 21:08.596
NOW, I'M JUST CHECKING
SOMETHING.

21:08.600 --> 21:10.921
AM I STILL IN CHARGE HERE?

21:10.930 --> 21:13.467
HUH?

21:13.470 --> 21:17.167
'CAUSE, YOU SEE,
A COUPLE DAYS AGO,

21:17.170 --> 21:19.400
SOME 09er COMES UP TO ME

21:19.410 --> 21:22.470
AND ASKS ME WHERE THE COKE IS
THAT HE ORDERED.

21:22.480 --> 21:26.075
HE SAID SOME BROWN-SKINNED BIKER
SOLD IT TO HIM.

21:26.080 --> 21:27.377
AND THEN A LITTLE BIRDIE

21:27.380 --> 21:29.371
TELLS ME THAT THE WITNESS
WHO CAME FORWARD

21:29.380 --> 21:30.847
IN LOGAN ECHOLLS' CASE

21:30.850 --> 21:34.559
WAS BOUGHT AND PAID FOR
BY THE FITZPATRICKS.

21:35.990 --> 21:38.322
AND IT GETS ME WONDERING.

21:38.330 --> 21:40.992
DID THE RULES CHANGE?

21:41.000 --> 21:42.820
HUH?

21:42.830 --> 21:45.264
ARE WE IN BUSINESS
WITH THESE POTATO HEADS

21:45.270 --> 21:46.692
AND I JUST
DON'T KNOW ABOUT IT?

21:46.700 --> 21:51.706
DID SOMEBODY HERE TRY
TO MAKE SOME EXTRA CASH?

21:53.270 --> 21:57.775
IT'S NOW OR NEVER, BOYS.

22:04.650 --> 22:06.447
GO ON.
GET OUT OF HERE.

22:06.450 --> 22:08.759
GO SCARE SOME OLD LADIES
OR SOMETHING.

22:17.670 --> 22:21.538
DO YOU REALLY THINK SOMEONE'S
WORKING FOR THE MICKS?

22:21.540 --> 22:23.633
I'M JUST ASKING.

22:23.640 --> 22:25.528
THE NIGHT
FELIX GOT KILLED,

22:25.540 --> 22:28.202
DID YOU SEE THE GUY
WHO CALLED THE COPS?

22:28.210 --> 22:30.303
NO, MAN.

22:30.310 --> 22:31.971
WHY NOT?

22:33.150 --> 22:35.015
YOU WERE THERE.

22:35.020 --> 22:38.683
THAT'S WHAT YOU TOLD ME.
THAT'S WHAT YOU TOLD THE COPS.

22:38.690 --> 22:41.011
YEAH, BUT THE COPS DIDN'T
HAVE THE WHOLE STORY.

22:41.020 --> 22:43.284
TALK.

22:43.290 --> 22:45.656
YOU WENT DOWN.
YOU WERE OUT.

22:45.660 --> 22:49.096
THEN Al-TER THAT, FELIX
WAS RUNNING THE SHOW.

22:49.100 --> 22:52.866
THUMPER, YOU AND DODY
GET WEEVIL BACK TO HIS HOUSE.

22:52.870 --> 22:55.191
GO! WE GOT
TO GET HIS BIKE HOME!

22:55.200 --> 22:58.909
WHY DON'T YOU
TAKE IT HOME?
'CAUSE WE GOT
AN EXTRA BIKE NOW, DOG.

22:58.910 --> 23:01.606
SULLEY, GO GET CERVANDO.
YOU BRING HIM BACK HERE.

23:01.610 --> 23:04.101
TELL HIM TO GET WEEVIL'S BIKE
BACK TO HIS PLACE. GO.

23:05.450 --> 23:07.941
YOU WANT TO JUMP?
HERE'S THE EDGE, GENIUS.

23:07.950 --> 23:11.078
YOU KNOW WHAT I ALWAYS WANTED
MY WHOLE LIFE?

23:11.090 --> 23:14.184
A BRIGHT-YELLOW S.U.V.

23:14.190 --> 23:17.580
FOR MY SURFBOARD...

23:19.330 --> 23:21.890
AND MY SNOWBOARD.

23:23.260 --> 23:25.194
BITCHING.

23:25.200 --> 23:27.498
UGH!

23:27.500 --> 23:30.139
[ HORN HONKING ]

23:39.480 --> 23:41.277
YOU TOLD ME
YOU SAW IT.

23:41.280 --> 23:44.078
HECTOR AND BOOTSY WAS THERE.
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?

23:44.090 --> 23:47.514
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED.

23:47.520 --> 23:48.680
COME ON, WEEVIL.

23:48.690 --> 23:50.988
WE NEED AS MANY GUYS
AS POSSIBLE.

23:50.990 --> 23:54.596
ONE RICH WHITE BOY'S WORD
AGAINST THE TWO OF US.

23:54.600 --> 23:56.591
WE DIDN'T TELL YOU
TO PROTECT YOU.

23:56.600 --> 23:58.921
IF YOU DIDN'T KNOW,
YOU'D NEVER HAVE TO LIE.

23:58.930 --> 24:02.639
ONE WAY OR ANOTHER, I'M GETTING
TO THE BOTTOM OF THIS, OKAY?

24:02.640 --> 24:05.131
WE'RE GONNA FIND OUT
WHAT'S TRUE.

24:06.940 --> 24:09.408
THE SIGNAL
IS STRONG HERE --

24:09.410 --> 24:10.775
STRONG LIKE A BULL.

24:10.780 --> 24:14.079
I THINK IT'S COMING
FROM INSIDE THE HOUSE.

24:14.080 --> 24:15.274
SHALL WE?

24:15.280 --> 24:16.872
LET'S.

24:16.880 --> 24:19.713
EXCELLENT WORK,
AS USUAL, "Q."

24:19.720 --> 24:22.917
RIGHT BACK AT YOU,
MR. BOND.

24:25.430 --> 24:27.898
YOU'VE GOT A PLAN,
RIGHT?

24:27.900 --> 24:29.822
YES.

24:31.700 --> 24:34.794
* IF I SAW HIM ON THE VIDEO *

24:37.170 --> 24:38.330
MISS MARS.

24:38.340 --> 24:41.002
I'M GLAD WE CAUGHT YOU
AT HOME.

24:41.010 --> 24:42.807
WOULD YOU MIND
IF WE USED YOUR PHONE?

24:42.810 --> 24:45.199
WE'RE BOTH
IN A BIT OF A HURRY.

24:47.080 --> 24:48.547
RIGHT.

24:48.550 --> 24:51.018
ACTUALLY, WE'RE HERE
TO SEE B--

24:51.020 --> 24:54.057
UH, VINCENT.

24:54.060 --> 24:59.555
WE HAVE SOME, UH,
"HOMEWORK" QUESTIONS.

25:00.430 --> 25:02.853
YOU ARE SO --

25:02.860 --> 25:05.590
DEAD. I KNOW. WHATEVER.
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO WAS ALL,

25:05.600 --> 25:07.488
"LET'S GO SEE
WHAT VINCENT'S DOING.

25:07.500 --> 25:10.037
I WONDER
WHAT VINCENT'S UP TO."

25:10.040 --> 25:15.569
I'D GREATLY PREFER IF NEXT TIME
YOU WOULD CALL FIRST.

25:15.580 --> 25:17.571
OKAY.

25:19.350 --> 25:21.170
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYS IN DISTANCE ]

25:21.180 --> 25:22.545
[ KNOCKING ]

25:22.550 --> 25:24.211
SON?

25:27.090 --> 25:28.284
VINCENT.

25:28.290 --> 25:31.589
Vincent: UM, PRIVATE
BASEMENT TIME, REMEMBER?

25:31.590 --> 25:33.126
YOU HAVE VISITORS.

25:33.130 --> 25:36.850
VERONICA MARS AND HER FRIEND
ARE HERE TO SEE YOU.

25:36.860 --> 25:39.363
TELL THEM I'M NOT HOME.

25:39.370 --> 25:41.065
THEY'RE RIGHT HERE, SON.

25:42.570 --> 25:44.561
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

25:45.810 --> 25:47.903
HEY, VINCENT,
WHATCHA DOING?

25:47.910 --> 25:52.301
IF THE GIRLS WOULD LIKE
SOME SNACKS AND SODA...

25:54.620 --> 25:56.645
LOOK, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

25:56.650 --> 25:58.709
WELL, WE WERE HOPING
TO BUST A MOVE,

25:58.720 --> 26:00.984
BUT THE SONG'S
ALMOST OVER.
[ ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]

26:00.990 --> 26:03.823
LOOK, I'M WORKING
ON MY MODELS.

26:03.830 --> 26:06.481
SO, IF THE PAINT DRIES,
THEN THE COLOR WON'T MATCH.

26:06.490 --> 26:08.390
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

26:08.400 --> 26:09.992
HMM.

26:10.000 --> 26:13.629
I WONDER WHY THEY'RE NOT
PLAYING ANOTHER SONG.

26:13.640 --> 26:15.392
I WANT YOU OUT OF HERE.

26:15.400 --> 26:18.301
WHY ARE YOU SO CRABBY?

26:18.310 --> 26:21.837
UM, BUTTERS...

26:21.840 --> 26:24.638
YOUR BLANKY'S BLINKING.

26:29.120 --> 26:31.213
HMM.

26:31.220 --> 26:32.812
I HAVE A THEORY.

26:32.820 --> 26:34.754
WANT TO HEAR IT?
HERE IT GOES.

26:34.760 --> 26:37.183
YOU ARE MARCOS WERE BUDS,
AND THEN YOUR DAD

26:37.190 --> 26:40.819
FOUND OUT ABOUT THE RADIO SHOW
YOU TWO DID TOGETHER.

26:40.830 --> 26:43.765
AND WHEN THE OLIVERAS FAMILY
DECIDED TO SUE,

26:43.770 --> 26:45.169
YOUR DAD
MADE YOU A DEAL.

26:45.170 --> 26:48.196
HE'D LET YOU KEEP
PUMPING UP THE VOLUME,

26:48.200 --> 26:51.658
BUT HE'D NEED RECORDINGS OF
MARCOS AND A KEY TO HIS HOUSE

26:51.670 --> 26:53.900
AND YOUR
RADIO KNOWLEDGE.

26:53.910 --> 26:57.971
WHAT? MY DAD DOESN'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT THE SHOW.

26:57.980 --> 27:01.609
A VICE-PRINCIPAL'S KID
RAGGING ON THE SCHOOL?

27:01.620 --> 27:03.815
HE WOULD KILL ME.

27:03.820 --> 27:05.845
MARCOS
QUIT THE RADIO SHOW

27:05.850 --> 27:08.455
MORE THAN A MONTH
BEFORE THE BUS CRASH.

27:08.460 --> 27:09.449
WHY?

27:09.460 --> 27:11.428
HE WENT TO CAMP.

27:11.430 --> 27:12.988
IT WAS OUT OF THE BLUE.

27:12.990 --> 27:14.890
HE MUST HAVE GOTTEN
TOSSED OFF BY A PONY

27:14.900 --> 27:16.788
'CAUSE HE CAME BACK
ALL WEIRD.

27:16.800 --> 27:19.496
HE CALLED AND SAID HE WASN'T
DOING THE SHOW ANYMORE.

27:19.500 --> 27:21.365
WELL, DID YOU
ASK HIM WHY?

27:21.370 --> 27:22.837
YEAH.

27:22.840 --> 27:24.705
WE GOT TOGETHER FOR HOT COCOA
AND CINNAMON TOAST

27:24.710 --> 27:27.270
AND TALKED ALL ABOUT
HIS FEELINGS.

27:27.270 --> 27:29.101
OH, LIKE GIRLS.

27:29.110 --> 27:32.739
CAPTAIN KRUNK REALLY
ELEVATED THE COMEDY.

27:32.750 --> 27:35.310
ALL I KNOW IS,
HE QUIT.

27:35.320 --> 27:38.710
THEN THE BUS CRASHED, AND
I REALLY DIDN'T HAVE A CHANCE

27:38.720 --> 27:40.608
TO ASK HIM ABOUT IT
AI-TER THAT.

27:40.620 --> 27:44.124
CAN YOU GO NOW,
PLEASE?

27:45.760 --> 27:48.228
I REALLY THINK
HE LIKES ME.

27:49.360 --> 27:52.921
Keith:
AND THAT'S WHERE THE RECORDINGS
OF HIS VOICE COME FROM.

27:52.930 --> 27:54.830
Carlos:
SO HE WAS ON THE RADIO.

27:54.840 --> 27:57.161
I GUESS THAT'S THE PERFECT PLACE
FOR A SHY KID.

27:57.170 --> 27:59.161
THAT'S PRETTY
ENTERPRISING, HUH?

27:59.170 --> 28:02.571
HE USED THE ANONYMITY
TO POKE FUN AT HIS CLASSMATES --

28:02.580 --> 28:04.275
SOMETIMES A BIT HARSH.

28:04.280 --> 28:07.272
IT'S POSSIBLE HE REALLY
OFFENDED SOME PEOPLE --

28:07.280 --> 28:09.874
ENOUGH TO MAKE THEM
HOLD A GRUDGE.

28:09.880 --> 28:11.279
COME ON.
MARCOS DIED.

28:11.290 --> 28:13.781
YOU REALLY THINK A KID'S
GONNA PURSUE REVENGE

28:13.790 --> 28:15.781
ON A CLASSMATE'S
GRIEVING PARENTS?

28:15.790 --> 28:17.417
I HAD MY DAUGHTER DO
A LITTLE DIGGING AT SCHOOL,

28:17.420 --> 28:20.821
AND SHE THINKS SOMETHING MIGHT
HAVE HAPPENED AT SUMMER CAMP --

28:20.830 --> 28:23.048
I'M SORRY.
YOUR DAUGHTER THINKS?

28:23.060 --> 28:26.427
THIS ISN'T KIDS' STUFF.
THIS ISN'T ABOUT SUMMER CAMP.

28:26.430 --> 28:27.829
IT'S ABOUT MONEY.

28:27.840 --> 28:28.989
THOSE GREEDY SONS OF BITCHES
AT THE DISTRICT

28:29.000 --> 28:30.490
ARE TRYING
TO SHUT US UP.

28:30.500 --> 28:33.503
I JUST WANT TO MAKE SURE WE LOOK
AT EVERY POSSIBILITY.

28:33.510 --> 28:38.709
LOOK, WE'VE GOT THREE DAYS
TO SETTLE OR DROP THIS SUIT.

28:38.710 --> 28:40.246
WE KNOW WHO'S DOING IT.

28:40.250 --> 28:42.218
YOU JUST HAVE TO FIND SOMETHING
THAT PROVES IT.

28:44.920 --> 28:47.013
I'M HEADING OVER
TO THE OLIVERAS' HOUSE.

28:47.020 --> 28:48.419
IT'S THEIR
BOWLING NIGHT,

28:48.420 --> 28:50.786
SO I'D FIGURED I'D DO
A LITTLE STAKEOUT,

28:50.790 --> 28:52.929
SEE IF I CAN'T CATCH THE GUY
IN THE ACT.

28:52.930 --> 28:54.989
Veronica: GOOD LUCK.

29:00.940 --> 29:04.205
IF MR. OLIVERAS DOESN'T
THINK CAMP IS IMPORTANT,

29:04.210 --> 29:07.338
HE'S FORGETTING HOW BRUTAL
TEENAGERS CAN BE.

29:07.340 --> 29:11.845
HERE IT IS.
ITEMIZED CHARGES FOR JULY.

29:11.850 --> 29:13.602
CAMP SELFQUEST.

29:13.610 --> 29:15.111
NOT TO BE MISTAKEN

29:15.120 --> 29:17.839
FOR THE ELF-HUNTING CAMP
OF A SIMILAR NAME.

29:17.850 --> 29:20.239
"CAMP SELFQUEST
IS AN INTENSIVE PROGRAM

29:20.250 --> 29:23.788
"FOR TEENS STRUGGLING
WITH THEIR SEXUALITY.

29:23.790 --> 29:25.280
"SELFQUEST OFFERS A UNIQUE PLAN

29:25.290 --> 29:27.997
"PROVEN TO REDIRECT TEENS
TO A MORE TRADITIONAL,

29:28.000 --> 29:29.422
"HEALTHIER LIFESTYLE.

29:29.430 --> 29:33.526
SELFQUEST CAN MOTIVATE
A PERMANENT CHANGE."

29:33.530 --> 29:37.432
MARCOS WAS GAY?

29:37.440 --> 29:39.431
[ BEEPING ]

29:43.380 --> 29:45.075
[ BEEPING STOPS ]

29:53.550 --> 29:54.858
WHO ARE YOU?

29:54.860 --> 29:57.385
I LIVE NEXT DOOR.
I'M JUST A NEIGHBOR.

29:57.390 --> 30:00.279
YOU ALWAYS WAIT TILL
BOWLING NIGHT TO COME CALLING?

30:00.290 --> 30:04.090
I CAME OVER TO BORROW
A COUPLE OF BEERS, OKAY?

30:04.100 --> 30:08.196
MY WIFE WON'T LET ME
KEEP BEER IN THE HOUSE.

30:10.910 --> 30:12.263
OW.

30:12.270 --> 30:14.033
SO YOU COME OVER HERE,
TOSS BACK A FEW,

30:14.040 --> 30:15.905
MAYBE TURN AROUND
A FEW PICTURES,

30:15.910 --> 30:17.332
SPRAY A LITTLE COLOGNE?

30:17.340 --> 30:19.570
YOU THINK YOUR WIFE
WOULD EASE UP ON YOU A BIT

30:19.580 --> 30:22.572
IF YOU HAD ENOUGH PROPERTY
TO EXTEND YOUR HOUSE?

30:22.580 --> 30:24.241
WHAT?

30:24.250 --> 30:26.286
YOU'RE LOOKING TO BUY THIS
PLACE. HOW BAD DO YOU WANT IT?

30:26.290 --> 30:30.454
I CAME HERE FOR THE BEER.
ASK CARLOS.

30:32.730 --> 30:34.698
GO GET YOUR BEER.

30:34.700 --> 30:36.452
I'M GOOD.

30:50.380 --> 30:52.848
[ SIGHS ]

31:30.880 --> 31:34.259
MR. OLIVERAS? KEITH MARS HERE.

31:34.260 --> 31:35.818
A COUPLE QUESTIONS FOR YOU.

31:35.820 --> 31:39.654
DOES YOUR NEIGHBOR ROUTINELY
KEEP BEER IN YOUR FRIDGE?

31:39.660 --> 31:41.992
HE DOES?

31:42.000 --> 31:43.695
AND HE HAS THE ALARM CODE?

31:43.700 --> 31:45.429
OKAY.

31:45.430 --> 31:49.332
SECOND THING -- ANOTHER TOY BUS
APPEARED, IN YOUR FISH TANK.

31:49.340 --> 31:52.332
I FOUND A SCRAP OF PAPER
IN YOUR WASTEBASKET

31:52.340 --> 31:54.672
WITH YOUR ALARM CODE
WRITTEN ON IT.

31:54.680 --> 31:58.673
IT'S SCRIBBLED ON THE BACK OF
SOME SIMON AND STERN LETTERHEAD.

31:58.680 --> 32:00.841
YEAH.

32:00.850 --> 32:04.013
THE SCHOOL DISTRICT 'S LAW FIRM.

32:04.020 --> 32:07.114
I THOUGHT THAT
WOULD MAKE YOU HAPPY.

32:07.120 --> 32:10.317
YEP. I'LL BRING IT
TO THE DEPOSITION.

32:10.320 --> 32:13.426
YOU'RE WELCOME, MR. OLIVERAS.

32:29.510 --> 32:30.977
[ SIGHS ]

32:30.980 --> 32:32.641
WHAT IS WRONG WITH PEOPLE?

32:45.860 --> 32:48.499
WAKE UP,
SLEEPING BEAUTY.

32:52.700 --> 32:55.089
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?

32:55.100 --> 32:56.658
IT'S THE "PEOPLE'S COURT,"
JUNIOR.

32:56.670 --> 33:00.561
YOU'RE ON TRIAL
FOR THE MURDER OF FELIX TOOMBS.

33:00.570 --> 33:02.800
SORRY I DON'T HAVE A BIBLE
FOR YOU TO SWEAR ON,

33:02.810 --> 33:05.677
BUT I'LL GET THE WHOLE TRUTH
AND NOTHING BUT THE TRUTH,

33:05.680 --> 33:07.102
SO HELP ME, GOD.

33:08.950 --> 33:10.212
THAT'S YOUR JUDGE
AND JURY.

33:10.220 --> 33:13.018
I'M THE PROSECUTION.

33:13.020 --> 33:17.013
YOU -- YOU GET
TO REPRESENT YOURSELF.

33:17.020 --> 33:20.387
[ DIALING ]

33:20.390 --> 33:24.224
THE FIRST QUESTION
FOR THE DEFENDANT --

33:24.230 --> 33:28.269
WHAT HAPPENED TO FELIX
THAT NIGHT ON THE BRIDGE?

33:28.270 --> 33:31.569
I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T KNOW.

33:37.110 --> 33:39.476
HE'S ALL YOURS, JUDGE.

33:44.790 --> 33:47.987
NO! NO! NO!

33:47.990 --> 33:49.218
OH, COME ON, MAN!

33:49.220 --> 33:51.882
ONE IN SIX
SAYS YOU TAKE A BULLET.

33:51.890 --> 33:53.380
NO, COME ON.
COME ON, MAN!

33:55.000 --> 33:56.649
[ GUN CLICKS ]

33:56.660 --> 33:57.922
OH, JESUS!

33:57.930 --> 33:59.192
[ SIGHS ]

33:59.200 --> 34:00.428
I'LL ASK YOU AGAIN.

34:00.430 --> 34:02.193
LOOK, I --
WHAT HAPPENED?!

34:02.200 --> 34:04.202
I CAN'T REMEMBER, OKAY?

34:04.210 --> 34:05.700
I SWEAR TO GOD,
I CAN'T REMEMBER.

34:05.710 --> 34:08.429
DAMN IT, MAN!
I'M TELLING YOU THE TRUTH!

34:08.440 --> 34:12.046
YOU'RE A KILLER, AREN'T YOU,
BOY? JUST LIKE YOUR OLD MAN.

34:12.050 --> 34:14.075
OH, GOD.

34:14.080 --> 34:15.445
PLEASE! PL--

34:15.450 --> 34:17.008
NO! NO!

34:17.020 --> 34:18.885
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO! NO!

34:18.890 --> 34:20.778
[ CLICKS ]

34:20.790 --> 34:23.088
OH, STOP, PLEASE.

34:23.090 --> 34:24.978
OKAY,
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.

34:24.990 --> 34:27.026
DAMN IT, MAN.
I SWEAR.

34:27.030 --> 34:28.292
DON'T TALK TO ME.

34:28.300 --> 34:31.224
IT'S THE JUDGE
YOU GOT TO CONVINCE.

34:31.230 --> 34:32.595
PLEASE.
I'M TELLING THE TRUTH.

34:32.600 --> 34:34.261
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING!
I SWEAR TO GOD!

34:34.270 --> 34:37.660
YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK
THE PROBLEM IS?

34:37.670 --> 34:40.104
THIS BOY DON'T CARE
ABOUT HIS HANDS.

34:40.110 --> 34:42.601
LET'S TRY SOME MORE VALUABLE
REAL ESTATE.

34:43.380 --> 34:45.644
OH, COME ON, MAN. NO.

34:45.650 --> 34:46.605
NO!

34:46.610 --> 34:48.043
[ GUN COCKS ]
NO! PLEASE!

34:48.050 --> 34:49.449
PLEASE DON'T DO THIS.

34:49.450 --> 34:52.715
COME ON. PLEASE DON'T.
PLEASE DON'T!

34:52.720 --> 34:53.846
UHH! PLEASE!

34:53.850 --> 34:56.978
LISTEN TO ME.
WHY WOULD I LIE, YOU GUYS?

34:56.990 --> 34:58.981
COME ON, MAN.
PLEASE.

34:58.990 --> 35:00.787
WE'RE DONE
FOR THE NIGHT.

35:07.830 --> 35:11.209
GIVE ME A HAND, MAN. I THINK
HE MIGHT HAVE WET HIMSELF.

35:43.000 --> 35:44.661
[ DIALING ]

35:46.440 --> 35:48.499
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

35:50.880 --> 35:52.347
IS IT DONE?

35:52.350 --> 35:55.114
OH, IT'S JUST GETTING STARTED,
WEEVS.

35:55.120 --> 35:59.819
YOU HAVE NO IDEA THE HELL
YOU JUST BROUGHT ON YOURSELF.

36:04.230 --> 36:06.186
FISH STICKS
AND CHOCOLATE MILK.

36:06.190 --> 36:08.226
YUCK. THAT CAN'T
BE GOOD FOR YOU.

36:08.230 --> 36:09.652
CAN YOU GRADUATE
ALREADY?

36:09.660 --> 36:12.527
WHAT DID MARCOS TELL YOU
ABOUT CAMP SELFQUEST?

36:12.530 --> 36:14.589
WHAT THE HELL
IS CAMP SELFQUEST?

36:14.600 --> 36:18.161
IT'S THE DEPROGRAMMING CAMP
MARCOS' PARENTS SENT HIM TO.

36:18.170 --> 36:20.331
YOU KNOW,
TO MAKE HIM UN-GAY.

36:20.340 --> 36:23.468
MARCOS WASN'T GAY.

36:23.480 --> 36:25.209
YOU SURE ABOUT THAT?

36:25.210 --> 36:26.404
POSITIVE.

36:26.410 --> 36:28.469
HE TALKED ABOUT CHICKS
ALL THE TIME.

36:28.480 --> 36:30.141
HE WASN'T A FAIRY.

36:30.150 --> 36:32.618
HE WAS PLAYBOY-LOVING
BOOTY HOUND.

36:32.620 --> 36:36.351
DO ME A FAVOR.
NEVER DESCRIBE ME.

36:36.360 --> 36:38.749
HE WAS ALL ABOUT GIRLS --
ALL THE TIME.

36:38.760 --> 36:41.957
HE ALMOST GOT HIS ASS KICKED
FOR IT ONCE.

36:41.960 --> 36:43.359
BY THE GIRL?

36:43.360 --> 36:45.396
BY HER JEALOUS BOYFRIEND.

36:45.400 --> 36:48.665
OKAY. OKAY.

36:51.710 --> 36:55.237
"SORRY, BUT I'VE GOT
A JEALOUS BOYFRIEND

36:55.240 --> 36:57.003
WHO KNEW I LIKED HIM, SO..."

36:57.010 --> 37:00.047
MAYBE THE SECRET ADMIRER
CAN GIVE ME AN ANSWER.

37:00.050 --> 37:02.678
"FREE CONCERT TICKETS
FOR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS.

37:02.680 --> 37:04.648
"THE RADIO BROADCAST ALLIANCE

37:04.650 --> 37:06.914
"IS SEEKING STUDENTS FOR A
SURVEY IN CONCERT PROMOTING.

37:06.920 --> 37:13.621
TO APPLY, PLEASE CALL
619-555-0127 IMMEDIATELY."

37:14.730 --> 37:16.857
I'M SORRY
I'M A LITTLE LATE.

37:16.860 --> 37:18.054
THAT'S FINE.

37:18.060 --> 37:19.493
OUR LAWYER SAID
THERE'D BE A FEW PAPERS

37:19.500 --> 37:21.092
THAT YOU'D HAVE
TO SIGN FOR US

37:21.100 --> 37:23.989
IN ADDITION TO TESTIFYING
ABOUT WHAT YOU DISCOVERED.

37:24.000 --> 37:25.968
EXCUSE US A SECOND.

37:30.680 --> 37:35.140
BEFORE I'M DEPOSED, THERE'S
SOMETHING I NEED CLEARED UP.

37:35.150 --> 37:36.549
WHAT'S THAT, KEITH?

37:36.550 --> 37:38.541
I FOUND FISH FOOD
FLOATING IN THE AQUARIUM.

37:38.550 --> 37:41.713
FOR THE LIFE OF ME,
I CAN'T MAKE SENSE OUT OF IT.

37:42.960 --> 37:47.158
I SUPPOSE THE GUY WHO BROKE IN
DECIDED TO...

37:47.160 --> 37:48.718
FEED THE FISH.

37:54.970 --> 37:58.565
I KNOW THIS HARASSMENT --
WHATEVER THE CAUSE --

37:58.570 --> 38:00.868
MUST HAVE BEEN TERRIBLE
FOR YOU.

38:00.870 --> 38:04.237
AND I FEEL BAD
I DIDN'T CATCH HIM RED-HANDED.

38:04.240 --> 38:05.878
BUT I CAN'T HELP
BUT WONDER

38:05.880 --> 38:08.872
IF SOMEONE LEI-T
THAT LAST TOY BUS

38:08.880 --> 38:12.543
AND THAT SCRAP OF PAPER
FOR ME TO FIND.

38:12.550 --> 38:17.351
I'M AFRAID YOU DON'T WANT ME
TESTIFYING, MR. OLIVERAS.

38:17.360 --> 38:20.887
I SUGGEST YOU TAKE
THE SETTLEMENT.

38:28.170 --> 38:31.298
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

38:32.370 --> 38:34.531
HELLO?
RADIO BROADCAST ALLIANCE.

38:34.540 --> 38:36.770
[ Dial tone ]

38:41.480 --> 38:43.243
ONE REVERSE PHONE BOOK LATER,

38:43.250 --> 38:47.619
AND I'VE GOT THE ADDRESS
OF MARCOS' SECRET ADMIRER...

38:47.620 --> 38:50.487
AND HOPEFULLY
THE NOT-SO-LOYAL GIRLFRIEND

38:50.490 --> 38:53.323
OF THE CRAZY,
JEALOUS BOYFRIEND.

38:54.560 --> 38:55.891
VERONICA MARS.

38:55.900 --> 38:57.356
ROXIE.

38:57.360 --> 39:00.295
I HAVE A COUPLE QUESTIONS
FOR YOU ABOUT MARCOS OLIVERAS.

39:00.300 --> 39:01.597
WHAT ABOUT HIM?

39:01.600 --> 39:03.136
COME ON.
DON'T PLAY COY.

39:03.140 --> 39:06.507
YOU SENT ME AN E-MAIL.
YOU CALLED AND HUNG UP.

39:06.510 --> 39:07.909
NO, I DIDN'T.

39:07.910 --> 39:10.902
RYAN, YOU DIDN'T FORGET
MY MILK SHAKE, DID YOU?

39:10.910 --> 39:14.073
DO YOU HAVE
AN IDIOT BROTHER, TOO?

39:20.520 --> 39:22.659
YOU CAN GET ME LATER.

39:22.660 --> 39:26.528
RYAN, I THINK I'LL
GET YOU RIGHT NOW.

39:26.530 --> 39:29.522
I USED TO LISTEN TO THE SHOW
RELIGIOUSLY.

39:29.530 --> 39:31.760
I DIDN'T KNOW MARCOS
AT SCHOOL.

39:31.770 --> 39:34.637
I-I JUST KNEW WHO HE WAS
ON THE RADIO.

39:34.640 --> 39:38.292
I WAS PRETTY MUCH
IN LOVE WITH HIM.

39:38.300 --> 39:39.938
MARCOS AND BUTTERS --

39:39.940 --> 39:42.204
THEY SIGNED OUT THIS REVERB MIKE
FROM BROADCAST JOURNALISM.

39:42.210 --> 39:45.338
I HEARD IT USED IN THE SHOW,
SO I KNEW IT WAS THEM.

39:45.350 --> 39:47.545
I TOLD THEM
I WAS A FAN.

39:47.550 --> 39:50.678
THUS BEGAN
OUR BEAUTIFUL FRIENDSHIP.

39:50.680 --> 39:53.342
SO, YOU GUYS WERE
LIKE A COUPLE?

39:53.350 --> 39:54.817
[ CHUCKLES ]
I WISH.

39:54.820 --> 39:58.688
MORE LIKE I WAS MADLY IN LOVE
AND 100% GAY,

39:58.690 --> 40:03.696
AND HE LIKED ME AS A FRIEND
AND WAS SEXUALLY ON THE FENCE.

40:03.700 --> 40:06.897
I KEPT TRYING
TO SUBTLY PUSH HIM OVER.

40:06.900 --> 40:10.688
I WAS GIVING HIM A BACK RUB
THIS ONE TIME,

40:10.700 --> 40:12.702
AND HIS PARENTS CAME IN.

40:12.710 --> 40:16.532
FOR SOME REASON,
SEEING THEIR SHIRTLESS SON

40:16.540 --> 40:19.839
WITH A BOY STRADDLING HIM
WAS UPSETTING.

40:19.850 --> 40:22.011
THEY SHIPPED HIM OFF
TO CAMP HOMOPHOBY

40:22.020 --> 40:25.080
AND MADE HIM PROMISE
TO NEVER SEE ME AGAIN.

40:26.420 --> 40:28.479
AND THEN HE DIED.

40:28.490 --> 40:31.584
NO.

40:31.590 --> 40:34.798
AND THEN HE WAS FORCED
TO DO NORMAL THINGS,

40:34.800 --> 40:37.928
LIKE GO ON FIELD TRIPS
TO BASEBALL GAMES.

40:37.930 --> 40:40.922
MARCOS IS DEAD
FOR ONE REASON --

40:40.930 --> 40:44.434
BECAUSE HE WAS DESPERATE
TO WIN BACK HIS PARENTS.

40:45.510 --> 40:48.775
STILL, THE OLIVERASES
LOST THEIR SON.

40:48.780 --> 40:52.079
THOSE PRANKS
REALLY HURT THEM.

40:52.080 --> 40:53.604
GOOD.

40:53.610 --> 40:55.749
THAT WAS THE IDEA.

40:57.620 --> 41:00.111
I'M SORRY I'VE BEEN
SO OUT OF IT LATELY.

41:00.120 --> 41:03.510
I GUESS IT'S JUST
A CONFUSING TIME, YOU KNOW?

41:03.520 --> 41:06.557
I DON'T KNOW WHY
YOU'RE SO CONFUSED.

41:10.100 --> 41:13.888
YOU EITHER WANT TO SAVE ME,
OR YOU DON'T.

41:13.900 --> 41:17.495
YOU KNOW YOU'RE
THE ONLY ONE WHO CAN.

41:17.500 --> 41:20.037
* KEEPING SECRETS... *

41:40.890 --> 41:46.021
* OCEAN CITY GIRL IS FADING *

41:50.470 --> 41:52.529
* OCEAN CITY GIRL... *

41:52.540 --> 41:54.098
OH, MY GOD.
